# Why: Overlay 024 replaced the user-facing "Documenso" copy across routes,
#      and our asset commit replaced the static favicon/logo PNG files. But
#      the platform's PRIMARY brand surface — the inline `<BrandingLogo>` and
#      `<BrandingLogoIcon>` SVG components — are React components with the
#      Documenso wordmark / seal embedded as path data. Those didn't change.
#      Result: post-deploy, every signed-in page still showed the Documenso
#      wordmark in the app header even though everything else read "Pacta".
#
#      This overlay replaces both inline SVG components with the Pacta seal
#      design (matching `packages/bizrethink/branding/pacta-symbol.svg`).
#
#      Three files modified:
#
#      1. apps/remix/app/components/general/branding-logo.tsx
#         Horizontal lockup (seal on left, "pacta" wordmark on right). Uses
#         currentColor for all fills/strokes so it inherits text color from
#         parent (matches upstream's <BrandingLogo className="text-foreground
#         h-6" /> pattern). Wordmark rendered as <text> element with system-
#         font fallback chain — keeps the SVG payload tiny vs converting the
#         letterforms to paths.
#
#      2. apps/remix/app/components/general/branding-logo-icon.tsx
#         Square seal-only mark for ultra-small contexts (mobile signing-page
#         header). Same currentColor approach.
#
#      3. apps/remix/app/routes/_unauthenticated+/_layout.tsx
#         Added <BrandingLogo /> above the unauthenticated form card. Upstream
#         Documenso renders signin / signup / verify-email with no logo,
#         relying solely on the background pattern for brand context. We add
#         the Pacta lockup so signed-out screens carry platform branding too.
#
#      Fragility: LOW-MED. The component files have stable APIs (just an SVG
#      attributes prop). Upstream rarely changes these — when they do, we
#      keep ours. The unauthenticated layout edit is a single import + 3-line
#      JSX block; trivial to merge.
#
#      Trade-off: rendering the wordmark via <text> means it depends on the
#      browser's font fallback chain. We've spec'd a thorough chain
#      (-apple-system → BlinkMacSystemFont → Segoe UI → system-ui → Helvetica
#      Neue → sans-serif) that yields acceptable rendering on macOS / Windows
#      / Linux / iOS / Android. If pixel-perfect cross-OS consistency becomes
#      important later, convert "pacta" letterforms to SVG paths via a font
#      converter (~30 min one-time work).
#
# Files modified (full file diffs in commit):
#   apps/remix/app/components/general/branding-logo.tsx
#   apps/remix/app/components/general/branding-logo-icon.tsx
#   apps/remix/app/routes/_unauthenticated+/_layout.tsx
